      • handleError

        public void handleError(java.lang.Throwable rCaught)
        Handles the failure of an asynchronous call. The handling differs if the exception is recoverable or not. If not, a message will be displayed to the user. If the exception is a recoverable exception a rollback to the previous interaction will be done. The user can then input the data again.
